# Supabase Schema And RLS

- Treat migrations as production schema history; prefer additive, explicit changes over destructive rewrites.
- Preserve or intentionally update RLS whenever schema changes affect data access.
- Think through impact on `profiles`, `programs`, `practices`, `checkins`, `messages`, `journey_entries`, and `push_tokens`.
- Keep auth-trigger behavior in mind when changing user creation or profile assumptions.
- If realtime tables or storage policies are affected, update them deliberately in the same migration when needed.
- Write SQL that is readable and safe to review, with comments only where the intent is not obvious.
